"Beigl P., Salhofer S.","Comparison of ecological effects and costs of communal waste management systems",2004,"Resources, Conservation and Recycling","41","2",,"83","102",,,10.1016/j.resconrec.2003.08.007,"http://www.scopus.com/inward/record.url?eid=2-s2.0-1842559889&partnerID=40&md5=b3551aec8b9528d52fbd968468e7dc46","Department of Waste Management, BOKU, Univ. Nat. Rsrc. Appl. Life Sci. V., Muthgasse 107, A-1190 Vienna, Austria","Beigl, P., Department of Waste Management, BOKU, Univ. Nat. Rsrc. Appl. Life Sci. V., Muthgasse 107, A-1190 Vienna, Austria; Salhofer, S., Department of Waste Management, BOKU, Univ. Nat. Rsrc. Appl. Life Sci. V., Muthgasse 107, A-1190 Vienna, Austria","The selection of an appropriate ""optimal"" recycling alternative has to take into consideration both the ecological and economic effects of the entire life-cycle. The aim of this paper is to compare different waste management systems by means of a life-cycle assessment (LCA) and a cost comparison. The analysis uses data regarding the amount of household waste generated, collected and treated in a selected area in Austria. For this purpose, model-based scenarios with recycling and separate collection as well as scenarios without recycling were created. The database covers the amounts of household waste generated in the different collection schemes, the transport distances by private delivery and by regional waste management companies and data on the waste treatment processes that are widely employed throughout Austria and Germany. The resulting life-cycle inventories have been assessed according to three impact categories relevant to this topic - the global warming potential (GWP), the acidification potential (AP) and the net energy use (NEU). The results include ecological impact analyses and cost comparisons for the overall waste management systems and the waste management systems for the individual waste types - waste paper, plastic packaging, metal packaging and waste glass. Finally, a sensitivity analysis should prove the validity of the results for regions with transport distances differing from those in the area under analysis. © 2003 Elsevier B.V. All rights reserved.","Household waste; Life-cycle assessment; Recycling; Waste management; Waste management system; Waste transport","Costs; Ecosystems; Global warming; Life cycle; Plastics; Recycling; Sensitivity analysis; Waste paper; Ecological efects; Global warming potential (GWP); Life-cycle assessment (LCA); Waste management; life cycle analysis; recycling; waste management; waste treatment; acidification; area under the curve; article; Austria; cost; data analysis; data base; electric potential; energy; Germany; greenhouse effect; information processing; life cycle; recycling; validation process; waste management; Austria; Central Europe; Eurasia; Europe; Germany",,,,,,"Borken, J., Patyk, A., Reinhardt, G., (1999) Basisdaten für Ökologische Bilanzierungen, , Wiesbaden (Germany): Vieweg;; Buwal, (1997) Bewertung Von Oekobilanzen Mit der Methode der Oekologischen Knappheit - Oekofaktoren, , Bern (Switzerland): Eigenverlag;; Coopers, Lybrand, (1997) Cost-benefit Analysis of the Different Municipal Solid Waste Management Systems: Objectives and Instruments for the Year 2000, , Office for Official Publications of the European Communities, Final report. Luxembourg, Luxembourg;; Gallenkemper, B., Brunnert, M., Ölgemüller, D., (1992) Behältersysteme und Ihr Einfluss Auf Die Verwertung, , Münster (Germany): Eigenverlag;; Hartard, S., Entwicklung einer Indikatorenmethode zur Effizienzprüfung von Getrenntsammelsystmen in der Abfallwirtschaft (2000) Schriftenreihe des Lehrstuhls Abfallwirtschaft und des Lehrstuhl Siedlungswasserwirtschaft, , Bauhausuniversität Weimar [Hrsg.], Berlin (Germany): Rhombos Verlag;; Harvey, L.D.D., Box models of the terrestrial biosphere (2000) The Carbon Cycle, , Wigley, TML, Schimel, DS, editors. Cambridge (UK): Cambridge University Press;; (1994) Vergleichende Untersuchun